14 WHEREAS, after retiring from state politics, Ed and his wife, Janet, moved to Highlands,
15 North Carolina, where they built a successful furniture and decorator showroom for over 20
16 years, demonstrating their entrepreneurial spirit; and
17 WHEREAS, Ed's lifelong commitment to public service and his passion for community
18 engagement were further evident through his active involvement in President Jimmy Carter's
19 campaign and his leadership role in bringing Rev. Billy Graham's series of services to
20 Georgia, enriching the lives of many Georgians; and
21 WHEREAS, Ed's legacy continues through his loving family, including his wife of over 70
22 years, Janet, as well as his children, grandchildren, and great-grandchildren, all of whom he
23 deeply cared for and whose lives he touched with kindness, wisdom, and dedication.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 join in honoring the life and memory of Clarence "Ed" Barker and express their deepest and
26 most sincere regret at his passing.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
29 Clarence "Ed" Barker.
